ls](https://github.com/hyperstart/hyperapp-devtools) have helped us along the way and will be the inspiration for what's coming next. \r\n\r\nStarting with V2 we'll be able to compile our apps for production _or_ development. Development mode will have useful warnings, logging, session import/export and time-traveling built right into your app!\r\n\r\nThis will work by [setting an environment variable](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Env), e.g., <samp>NODE_ENV=production</samp> or <samp>NODE_ENV=development</samp>. What will be default? \r\n\r\nFor CDN users, <samp>hyperapp.js</samp> will be the development build and a new <samp>hyperapp.min.js </samp> will be available.\r\n\r\n","performed_via_github_app":null,"score":1.0}]}
